text: An old mall, recently repainted, this mall was built in the late 60s and was the first Air Con mall in the whole Hougang.

Nothing much in this place except a comic book store, a watch service centre, a salon and a place selling baby items. Very quiet. Toilets are inconveniently located behind the building. Its beside Pat's School House.

Owner at ActiveCardGames is quite friendly and prices there are reasonable. Shop has quite a few tables for TCG games and hosts weekly tournaments with balanced prize pool for all participants. Recommended for beginner players who's looking to start playing competitively
On top of the stores there are Studio apartments where the owners has taken advantage renting out a single room for 1300 to 1400 SGD. Which doesn't make any sence.
Free parking, got new Cafe and massage place, both quite good.
